      • createDrawingRectangle

        IDiagramDrawingNode createDrawingRectangle(IDiagramDrawingsLayer layer,
                                           java.lang.String drawingIdentifier,
                                           int x,
                                           int y,
                                           int w,
                                           int h)
        Creates a drawing rectangle.
        Parameters:
        layer - the layer to use
        drawingIdentifier - An identifier unique in the diagram, to be able to look for the graphic later. If null, an identifier will be automatically generated.
        x - the x coordinates of the top left corner.
        y - the y coordinates of the top left corner.
        w - the node width
        h - the node height
        Returns:
        the created graphic node.

      • unmask

        java.util.List<IDiagramGraphic> unmask(MObject element,
                                       int x,
                                       int y)
        Unmask a model element in a diagram.

        The model element is unmasked at the given position.

        Parameters:
        element - the model element to unmask.
        x - the x coordinates of the unmasking position.
        y - the y coordinates of the unmasking position.
        Returns:
        a list of all the new diagram graphics. Might be empty, but not null.
